                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13819977" author="mduerig" created="Tue, 12 Nov 2013 10:08:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(Commented out) test case at &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1540991&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1540991&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13820510" author="jukkaz" created="Tue, 12 Nov 2013 21:49:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Continuing from the previous discussions, I think we should decouple the task of namespace mapping from that of name/path validation. Otherwise we incur the performance overhead of validation in many cases where the simpler mapping would suffice, which is troublesome as the cost of validation has a notable performance impact on content access. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# GetNodeWithAdmin           C     min     10%     50%     90%     max       N
Oak-Tar                      1      15      15      16      17      51    3665
Oak-Tar (without r1538131)   1      20      20      21      21      82    2885
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus instead of focusing on the &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; return value of &lt;tt&gt;getOakPath&lt;/tt&gt; here, I&apos;d consider relaxing the mapper contract and looking at alternative ways of fulfilling the higher level API contracts/expectations that are affected by this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821077" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 08:55:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1174&quot; title=&quot;Inconsistent handling of invalid names/paths&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1174&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1174&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the current effect on the higher level contracts. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13946553" author="anchela" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2014 13:58:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;proposed patch for NamePathMapperImpl including enabling the tests for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1168&quot; title=&quot;Invalid JCR paths not caught&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1168&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1168&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1174&quot; title=&quot;Inconsistent handling of invalid names/paths&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1174&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1174&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (with some extensions)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13946606" author="jukkaz" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2014 14:30:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The changed indentation makes it a bit difficult to tell what changed, but IIUC you added the characters ], | and * as extra triggers for full path parsing, which is good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13946621" author="anchela" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2014 14:42:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;exactly... do you see any reason why this should have an impact on the overall performance? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13946653" author="jukkaz" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2014 15:07:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t be a problem performance-wise, as the switch statement is very fast.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13946702" author="anchela" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2014 15:49:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commited rev. 1581382&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13962859" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 12:47:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bulk close for the 0.20.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
